    "product_details_gLrgBJ": {
      "type": "product-details",
      "blocks": {
        "description_qpiTya": {
          "type": "description",
          "settings": {
            "description_heading": "Overview"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_TUUWYD": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Overview",
            "content": "<p>The AAW Z07 Hybrid In-Ear Monitor represents a groundbreaking acoustic redesign, featuring a tubeless and filter-free architecture. By eliminating restrictive sound tubes and acoustic dampers, the Z07 achieves exceptional phase coherence, zero tube-induced phase shift, and faster transient response.</p><p></p><p>At its core, the Z07 utilizes a seven-driver configuration governed by a true 3-way electronic crossover. A 10 mm titanium diaphragm dynamic driver anchors the sub-bass and bass frequencies, providing tight, structural bass control without unwanted bloom. The midrange and treble are rendered by six precise balanced armatures housed within a non-resonant, CNC-machined aluminium acoustic core.</p><p></p><p>To ensure long-term comfort and durability, the Z07 introduces the FitMorph™ Adaptive Fit System. This modular 3D-printed fitment holder comes in multiple configurations—including an option for a customized fit based on a physical ear impression—allowing users to tailor the shell's ergonomic stability while maintaining a secure seal with flexible liquid silicone ear tips. Furthermore, the FitMorph™ system integrates a replaceable 0.78 mm 2-pin socket, maximizing the monitor's lifespan and serviceability without requiring internal disassembly or shell destruction.</p><p></p><p>Tuned for reference transparency and featuring a 12 Ω impedance with 101 dB sensitivity, the AAW Z07 is designed for critical monitoring and audiophile reference listening.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_PAyNwP": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "True Tube-Free & Filter-Free Construction",
            "content": "<p>Unlike traditional IEMs that depend on long sound tubes, acoustic dampers, mechanical filters, and pressure-restrictive pathways, the Z07 eliminates all of these elements. Within the monitor, each driver is geometrically aligned inside the acoustic body, free from sound tubes, acoustic filters, and waveform restrictions. This design results in several advantages:<br/>-\tZero tube-induced phase shift<br/>-\tNo filter compression artifacts<br/>-\tFaster transient response<br/>-\tHigher dynamic efficiency<br/>-\tMore accurate multi-driver summation<br/>-\tNatural, unforced tonal decay<br/>The result is pure mechanical sound radiation, guided solely by geometry and crossover logic.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_n38dzJ": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "The FitMorph™ Adaptive Fit System",
            "content": "<p>The Z07 introduces the FitMorph™ system, a modular ergonomic solution allowing the monitor to conform to diverse ear anatomies and wearing preferences. The aluminium acoustic core is housed within a replaceable 3D-printed fitment holder, available in two configurations:<br/>-\tWith Shark Fin Stabilizer: offers maximum stability for stage use and extended sessions<br/>-\tWithout Shark Fin: provides a cleaner contour and pressure-free comfort, ideal for smaller ears<br/>Both versions are included, enabling users to optimize isolation versus openness, fine-tune insertion depth and lock-in feel, reduce listening fatigue, and personalize ergonomic pressure distribution. This mechanical system allows for ergonomic tuning without compromise.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_HffCBq": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Modular Longevity Philosophy",
            "content": "<p>The Z07 is engineered for long-term use as a reference instrument, not as a disposable product. Key design features include replaceable FitMorph™ outer shells, a replaceable 0.78 mm 2-pin socket module, a metal-core acoustic backbone, and the absence of tube or filter aging. These elements ensure years of serviceability, predictable ownership costs, and consistent acoustic performance over time—engineering designed for lifespan, not just initial performance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_Rt9FnT": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Sound Signature Philosophy",
            "content": "<p>The Z07 is tuned for reference transparency<br/>paired with authoritative low-end presence. The bass is deep, textured, fast,<br/>and pressure-controlled. The midrange is neutral, clean, and emotionally<br/>accurate. Treble is extended, airy, and non-fatiguing. Imaging is centered with<br/>layered depth, and the soundstage is wide, stable, and holographic. This<br/>monitor is designed for critical monitoring, audiophile reference listening,<br/>and professional long-session use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "collapsible_tab_XefaKL": {
          "type": "collapsible_tab",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Accessories and Warranty",
            "content": "<p>48\" Null Audio Brevity Max Copper 4.4/3.5 Modular Cable<br/>AAW Carrying Case<br/>3 Pairs LiquidMorph Silicone Tip(S/M/L)*<br/>3 Pairs AAW Short Stem Foam Tips(S/M/L)*<br/>3 Pairs AAW Silicone Tips (S/M/L)*<br/>1 Year Limited Warranty</p><p>* For Universal Fit Only</p>"
          }
        },
